Clearly not. This monster just roared and tried to ram Saaslin directly. Praise heaven, although Saaslin was large, it was still agile enough to dodge in time. However, Nissi couldn't help screaming, nearly sliding off Saaslin's smooth scales.
"How can we kill them?" Nissi shouted.
"Target their heads!"
"That's too difficult!"
Saaslin let out a roar, circling around and flying towards the mountain where he called home. The black monster followed closely, but when it was attacked by fire from behind, it showed some signs of panic. This monster had yet to realize it now had another opponent. Saaslin slowed down, then used its tail to strike the monster's head, causing it to deviate from its course, making the monster even more panicked.
The monster roared, hissing as he shot up into the air, constantly spewing something into the sky. Suddenly, everything turned pitch black, as if the monster was sucking in the light from the heavens and replacing it with eternal darkness.
Saaslin's vision went black, and he tried to retreat, but found himself colliding with tree branches before crashing to the ground. The monster seemed to know exactly where Saaslin fell, shooting towards him and dragging that cloud of darkness with it.
"Cayel!" Tenuk shouted, flying out of the cloud, circling in the air, trying to find Nissi and Saaslin below the darkness. "What should we do? Cayel…? Cayel, where are you?"
Nissi struggled to stand up. She felt sure she had broken several bones, but her strange, unnatural healing ability was already at work. Saaslin, however, lay motionless on the ground, propped up against a tree he had knocked over. Nissi forced herself towards Saaslin, but everything was pitch black and she could hardly see anything. Shadows everywhere, and things were screaming in the shadows.
A terrifying whip-like tail slammed into the ground, flipping Nissi over. She noticed the tail was wildly swinging, but the target didn't seem to be her. Nissi barely made out the monster roaring, scratching at the shadows it had created. Something was teleporting through the darkness, poised to strike at the monster.
Suddenly, a gunshot pierced the air, and the monster instantly quieted down, falling to the ground motionless. The surrounding darkness dissipated, revealing the truth. Cayel stood on top of the monster's corpse, holding a rifle, panting heavily.
"That... was one of the weirdest shadow jumps I've ever done... Tenot Cartaelor..." Cayel panted. For some reason, his eyes were glowing black, and a dark energy was surging within him. But just as Cayel started to speak, his organic armor regained its color, and his eyes returned to their normal yellow.
After a while, Nissi finally understood what had happened. They all knew that Cayel possessed peculiar shadow abilities, but he rarely used them because most people believed such abilities were extremely evil and terrifying. However, Nissi didn't know that Cayel could use this ability in any darkness. And from Cayel's reaction, he seemed quite surprised himself.
"Are you okay?" Nissi couldn't help asking.
"I'm fine. I killed that thing, and I'll be back to myself soon." Cayel looked at his "work," and at that moment, Tenuk landed beside him, reverting to his original Sbastre form.
Now the monster was no longer moving, and they could finally take a good look at what it was. Its skin was dark and glossy, covered in a sticky liquid that clung firmly to the monster's body. It had four wings and four legs, each ending in long claws, and two straight horns protruding from its skull.
Tenuk and Cayel hadn't even had the chance to ask what that thing was when a monster screamed and leaped out from nearby bushes. At that moment, a familiar car hit the side of the monster, sending it sliding a few meters until it stopped at Nissi's feet. Nissi didn't hesitate and grabbed the shotgun, firing a shot straight at the monster's head, killing it instantly.
"Ouch…" Revtvik muttered from the driver's seat, then awkwardly turned off the engine and climbed out of the truck. "Uh, I wasn't deliberately aiming for you. Are you guys okay?"
"You missed all the fun!" Tenuk said with a shake of his head. "Where did you go?"
"It's your fault for leaving me behind. I tried my best to catch up…" Revtvik sighed. "May I ask, what are these scary creatures?"
Revtvik's question was answered by Saaslin, who had already stood up. He was covered in wounds and scratch marks, looking a bit dazed, but his injuries didn't seem serious.
"You killed the Corrupter! Those infected monsters. When the Corruption attacked your gods, these creatures were left behind."
"You mean… we… helped kill the terrible god-monster?" Tenuk stammered.
"Yes, that's right. There might be more Corrupters. But I couldn't shoot them in the head. I don't have a gun. And it wouldn't be fair with two against one, right?" Saaslin walked up to Cayel and patted his head. "Thanks, little guy. You remind me of my old friend Arkady. Except you're not as ruthless, nor do you have the power to destroy the universe."
"Uh… thanks… I think…" Cayel shrugged. "So, uh, are we done with the mission?"
Nissi shrugged, picked up her camera, and took a few photos of the monsters that she was sure were dead. Then, she drew out her favorite knife – the beautiful Deathscythe – and began cutting one of the monster's horns. Next, she cut the other. However, just as Nissi finished the cuts, the monsters suddenly started burning on their own, quickly turning into ashes. The horns she had cut also turned to ashes.
"Well… there are pros and cons to that…" Nissi sighed. "At least I have photos."
